    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:1.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—",
          "en": "So I have heard. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:1.2",
          "pli": "ekaṃ samayaṃ sambahulā bhikkhū, kosalesu viharanti himavantapasse araññakuṭikāya uddhatā unnaḷā capalā mukharā vikiṇṇavācā muṭṭhassatino asampajānā asamāhitā vibbhantacittā pākatindriyā. ",
          "en": "Now at that time several mendicants were staying in the Kosalan lands, in a wilderness hut on the slopes of the Himalayas. They were restless, insolent, fickle, gossipy, loose-tongued, unmindful, lacking situational awareness and immersion, with straying minds and undisciplined faculties. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:2.1",
          "pli": "Atha kho jantu devaputto tadahuposathe pannarase yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: ",
          "en": "Then on the fifteenth day sabbath the god Jantu went up to those mendicants and addressed them in verse: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:3.1",
          "pli": "“Sukhajīvino pure āsuṃ, ",
          "en": "“The mendicants used to live happily, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:3.2",
          "pli": "bhikkhū gotamasāvakā; ",
          "en": "as disciples of Gotama. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:3.3",
          "pli": "Anicchā piṇḍamesanā, ",
          "en": "Desireless they sought alms; "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:3.4",
          "pli": "anicchā sayanāsanaṃ; ",
          "en": "desireless they used their lodgings. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:3.5",
          "pli": "Loke aniccataṃ ñatvā, ",
          "en": "Knowing that the world was impermanent "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:3.6",
          "pli": "dukkhassantaṃ akaṃsu te. ",
          "en": "they made an end of suffering. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:4.1",
          "pli": "Dupposaṃ katvā attānaṃ, ",
          "en": "But now they’ve made themselves hard to look after, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:4.2",
          "pli": "gāme gāmaṇikā viya; ",
          "en": "like chiefs in a village. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:4.3",
          "pli": "Bhutvā bhutvā nipajjanti, ",
          "en": "They eat and eat and then lie down, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:4.4",
          "pli": "parāgāresu mucchitā. ",
          "en": "unconscious in the homes of others. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:5.1",
          "pli": "Saṃghassa añjaliṃ katvā, ",
          "en": "Having raised my joined palms to the Saṅgha, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:5.2",
          "pli": "idhekacce vadāmahaṃ; ",
          "en": "I speak here only about certain people. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:5.3",
          "pli": "Apaviddhā anāthā te, ",
          "en": "They’re rejects, with no protector, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:5.4",
          "pli": "yathā petā tatheva te. ",
          "en": "just like those who have passed away. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:6.1",
          "pli": "Ye kho pamattā viharanti, ",
          "en": "I’m speaking about "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:6.2",
          "pli": "te me sandhāya bhāsitaṃ; ",
          "en": "those who live negligently. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:6.3",
          "pli": "Ye appamattā viharanti, ",
          "en": "To those who live diligently "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.25:6.4",
          "pli": "namo tesaṃ karomahan”ti. ",
          "en": "I pay homage.”"
        }
      ],
